&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;SCR Assistant Application Developer&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Permanent &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;37.5 hours per week&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;An exciting opportunity has arisen for an enthusiastic individual with excellent Web based Technology skills to join the Somerset Cancer Register (SCR) Team as an Assistant Application Developer.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are a friendly, dedicated team which works to maintain and improve SCR IT Products for our customers which have been developed in-house.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Assistant Application Developer role acts as a liaison between Application Development and Application Support teams and will also spend time providing technical support to users.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The post holder will focus on operational aspects of software development which may include analysis, specification, design (ergonomic and technical), programming, testing, documentation and maintenance of the Somerset Cancer Register web application using Microsoft Visual Studio .NET and other related web technologies.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Please note that the interview date is only approximate and could be subject to change.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details:&lt;/p&gt;
